-- General Atlantic to invest in Indian tech services firm CitiusTech
-- By Aditi Shah and Indulal PM in Mumbai
-- Thu Mar 20, 2014 09:42AM EDT
-- None



NEW DELHI, March 20 (Reuters) - India's CitiusTech said on Thursday U.S.-based buyout firm General Atlantic LLC has agreed to invest in the healthcare technology services and solutions provider to help it expand business globally.

While the company did not disclose the financial detail, a source with direct knowledge of the transaction told Reuters  General Atlantic would buy a 26 percent stake in CitiusTech for about $120 million.